{
  "comment": "Shared formula evaluator corpus. Both backend Python evaluator and frontend TS evaluator MUST produce identical EvalResult for every case. Each case parses `source`, resolves field refs by using display_name as field_id directly (case-insensitive), then evaluates against `row` (a {field_id -> value} mapping; keys are display_name.casefold()). expected.ok=true / value=<scalar | null>, or expected.ok=false / code=<error_code>. Numeric values compare via floating-point equality (a corpus assertion never compares 0.1+0.2 to 0.3 directly; results that involve binary fp drift are pinned by the corpus value to whatever both languages produce).",
  "cases": [
    {
      "name": "literal_number",
      "source": "42",
      "row": {},
      "expected": {"ok": true, "value": 42}
    },
    {
      "name": "literal_string",
      "source": "\"hello\"",
      "row": {},
      "expected": {"ok": true, "value": "hello"}
    },
    {
      "name": "literal_null",
      "source": "null",
      "row": {},
      "expected": {"ok": true, "value": null}
    },
